body_text:
@isalirezag Could you please elaborate on what you mean by using gpu 0 and 1. Tensors lie on just one card. The device context manager controlls the card to used for creating a new tensor.
Do you mean only card 0 and 1 should be made available to your PyTorch program?
Is CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES what your are looking for?

body:
@isalirezag Could you please elaborate on what you mean by using gpu 0 and 1. Tensors lie on just one card. The device context manager controlls the card to used for creating a new tensor.

Do you mean only card 0 and 1 should be made available to your PyTorch program?
Is [CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES](https://devblogs.nvidia.com/cuda-pro-tip-control-gpu-visibility-cuda_visible_devices/) what your are looking for?
